ABUJA – The coronavirus pandemic continued its spread in Nigeria with 16 new confirmed cases on Tuesday as announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). First the time since the end of first case was announced in Nigeria in February the disease has reached Katsina with one confirmed case on Tuesday according to NCDC.One more death was recorded on Tuesday to bring the total number of deaths associated with COVID-19 to six. On a happy note, the number of patients discharged increased from 25 to 44. This number includes the seven patients from Abuja earlier announced by the Minister of FCT, Muhammad Bello. The full NCDC report as announced on its Twitter handle is as follows: Sixteen new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 10 in Lagos, 2 in the FCT, 2 in Oyo, 1 in Delta and 1 in Katsina As at 09:30 pm 7th April there are 254 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Fourty-four have been discharged with six deaths https://t.co/UlDvzM3cUZ As at 09:30 pm 7th April, there are254 confirmed cases44 discharged6 deaths For more info-https://t.co/zQrpNeOfet Lagos- 130FCT- 50Osun- 20Oyo- 11Edo- 11Bauchi- 6Akwa Ibom- 5Kaduna- 5Ogun- 4Enugu- 2Ekiti- 2Rivers-2Benue- 1Ondo- 1Kwara- 2Delta- 1Katsina-1 ABUJA -  The coronavirus pandemic continues a steady rise in Nigeria as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) announcing four new cases late evening of Tuesday. According to the NCDC on its Twitter handle, three new cases were confirmed in the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja while one case happened… March 31, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - Akwa Ibom has joined the list of states with the coronavirus pandemic as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) confirmed fives cases in that state in its latest update on Tuesday night. Are you The five cases from Akwa Ibom are part of the 23 latest cases… April 1, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - The coronavirus pandemic worsens in Nigeria with the disease spreading to Rivers State, where the Nigeria Centre for Disea